title: DIARY- Top Economic Events to Sept 14
text:

** This Diary is filed daily ** WEDNESDAY, SEPTEMBER 2
WASHINGTON - Federal Reserve issues the Beige Book of economic conditions - 1800 GMT. STOCKHOLM - Swedish Central Bank holds monetary policy meeting (to Sept. 03). JAKARTA - Conference on "Future of Asian financing" in Indonesia. Speakers:- International Monetary Fund Managing Director Christine Lagarde, Reserve Bank of India Deputy Governor Urjit Patel, Bank of Japan Deputy Governor Hiroshi Nakaso, Indonesia Finance Minister Bambang Brodjonegoro and IMF Monetary and Capital Markets Department Division Chief Ulric Erickson von Allmen.
THURSDAY, SEPTEMBER 3 FRANKFURT - European Central Bank Governing Council meeting, followed by interest rate announcement and news conference - 1145 GMT. PARIS - French Finance Minister Michel Sapin holds a press conference - 0500 GMT. AOMORI, Japan - Bank of Japan board member Takahide Kiuchi speaks in Aomori - 0130 GMT. STOCKHOLM - Swedish Central Bank announces interest rate decision - 0730 GMT.
FRIDAY, SEPTEMBER 4
MISSOULA, United States - Federal Reserve Bank of Minneapolis President Narayana Kocherlakota speaks before a Town Hall open forum - 0100 GMT. RICHMOND, United States - Federal Reserve Bank of Richmond President Jeffrey Lacker speaks on "The Case Against Further Delay" before the Retail Merchants Association Economic Forecast breakfast - 1210 GMT. LONDON - Swedish Riksbank Deputy Governor Cecilia Skingsley speaks at Deutsche Bank's headquarter in London on the Swedish central bank's latest report - 0930 GMT. TOKYO - International Monetary Fund Deputy Director (Asia and Pacific Department) Kalpana Kochhar speaks at the IMF seminar - Reloading Abenomics: Priorities for the Needed Regime Shift - 0600 GMT. ANKARA - G20 Finance Ministers and Central Bank Governors meeting (to Sept. 5).
SATURDAY, SEPTEMBER 5 ANAKRA - German Finance Minister Wolfgang Schaeuble and ECB Governing Council member Jens Weidmann hold a press conference at G20 meeting - 0500 GMT.
MONDAY, SEPTEMBER 7 ISTANBUL, Turkey - Young Businessmen Association of Turkey (TUGIAD) hosts Young Entrepreneurs' Alliance (YEA), part of G20 summit (to Sept. 9). WEDNESDAY, SEPTEMBER 9
LONDON - Bank of England holds Monetary Policy Committee meeting (to Sept. 10). OTTAWA - Bank of Canada key policy interest rate announcement - 1400 GMT. THURSDAY, SEPTEMBER 10 LONDON - Bank of England announces rate decision - 1100 GMT. LONDON - Bank of England publishes the minutes of September policy meeting - 1100 GMT. FRIDAY, SEPTEMBER 11 LUXEMBOURG - Informal EU finance ministers meeting (to Sept. 12). MONDAY, SEPTEMBER 14 PARIS - ECB Governing Council member Christian Noyer delivers the opening speech at a conference to mark the 20th birthday of Bank of France Foundation - 0700 GMT.
